  "title": "Buimo Correctional Institution Inmates Mark PNG's 50th Independence Anniversary",
  "text": "Inmates at Buimo Correctional Institution in Lae, Morobe Province, are taking part in activities to celebrate Papua New Guinea’s 50th Independence Anniversary.\nThe program runs on September 1st – 5th, and 15th – 16th, 2025, under the theme “Year of Jubilee.”\nThe celebration carries the message from Leviticus 25:10: “Proclaim liberty throughout the land.”\nThe institution emphasized the theme “We Are Changed and Free” as part of its commemoration of the Golden Jubilee.\nBuimo inmates will join the rest of the country in marking this milestone, reflecting on freedom, change, and unity as Papua New Guinea celebrates 50 years of independence.",
